Project Summary: HW3 — CNN on CIFAR-10
This is a machine learning homework assignment implementing image classifiers from scratch using TensorFlow/Keras on the CIFAR-10 dataset, restricted to two classes (cat vs. dog). The goal is to achieve ≥70% binary classification accuracy.

What it does
The project has two parts:

Part 1 — Manual Convolution

Implement a custom 2D convolution layer (ManualConv2d in manual_convolution.py) from scratch — no using tf.nn.conv2d. It must support SAME and VALID padding.

Part 2 — Model Training

Build and train two classifiers on CIFAR-10 (cat/dog):

MLP (mlp.py) — a multi-layer perceptron (dense layers only)
CNN (cnn.py) — a convolutional neural network using the custom ManualConv2d layer
Both inherit from CifarModel (base_model.py), which defines the loss() and accuracy() interface (also to be implemented).

How to run
Local testing of convolution: python local_test.py

Runs sanity checks comparing ManualConv2d output against Keras's built-in Conv2D.

Training + testing the full model: python assignment.py

Requires setting LOCAL_TRAIN_FILE and LOCAL_TEST_FILE paths to the CIFAR-10 binary data files. Autograder uses ../data/train and ../data/test.

